    <title>Reliability of journeys on the Highways Agency’s motorway and A road network</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;h2 id="dft-business-plan-impact-indicator"&gt;DfT Business plan impact indicator&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Geographical coverage: England&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Information broken down by: national level aggregation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="latest-data"&gt;Latest data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provisional data show that 82.3% of journeys made on Highways Agency managed roads between November 2011 and October 2012 were ‘on time’. This is 0.3 percentage points lower than the previous rolling year, ending in September 2012..&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;During October 2012, provisional data show that 79.6% of journeys on Highways Agency’s motorway and ‘A’ road network were ‘on time’. This is 3.4 percentage points lower than the equivalent figure for October 2011.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The annual reliability measure consistently increased up to March 2012, but has fallen in the last seven months, and has now dropped below the level observed at the end of 2011. The recent downward trend in reliability reflects the substantial amount of rainfall experienced since spring compared with the same period in 2011. In fact, rainfall in each of the last seven months has been higher in 2012 compared to the same month in 2011.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://charts.dft.gov.uk/dft-business-plan/indicators/#01"&gt;Click here to view this data in an interactive chart&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of journeys on Highways Agency motorways and A roads deemed ‘on time’: monthly from June 2012&lt;/p&gt;

